newsitem.title: VIETNAM: Vietnam industrial output picks up - paper.
newsitem.headline: Vietnam industrial output picks up - paper.

text.p: Vietnam's industrial output in the first nine months of this year was 14 percent higher than during the same period of 1995, the official Saigon Giai Phong newspaper said on Monday.
The figures indicated a pick-up from August, when year-on-year output growth was 13.4 percent, and took the rate of expansion into the government's 1996 target range of 14.0-14.5 percent.
The year-on-year rate of growth in industrial production in January-September 1995 was 14.3 percent.
Officials at the Government Statistics Office were not available to confirm the state-run newspaper's report.
The semi-official Vietnam Economic Times gave different figures that showed a 13.5-percent rise in output compared with the first nine months of 1995.
Saigon Giai Phong said state-sector production rose by 13.3 percent this month and non state-sector output was up 13.0 percent. Industry with foreign investment saw its output rise 17.0 percent.
